Condition : 3 - Other than the repairs works for the decorative tiling to the entrance hall, hallway and toilet walls (Condition 4), the repair and redecoration works shall be carried out in full accordance with the Schedule of Dilapidation. However, where new materials are required, product specification/details and samples of these materials shall first be submitted to the Local Planning Authority for approval prior to their installation. No new materials shall be installed or fitted until the details/samples are approved. These include:
"	Roof tiles; 
"	Cast iron downpipes; 
"	New taps - original taps (if any have survived) should be retained and reproduced; 
"	Sinks (if any are proposed);  
"	Basement door; 
"	Ventilation grilles;
"	Radiator; 
"	New flooring in toilet - including any tiles, vinyl or others;
"	Wall tiles (not related to those in Condition 4); and 
"	Windows.

Reason: In the interests of the appearance of the Listed Building and to ensure a satisfactory appearance of the development, and to comply with the following Development Plan policies for Merton: policy HC1 of the London Plan 2021, policy CS14 of Merton's Core Planning Strategy 2011 and policies DM D2, DM D3 and DM D4 of Merton's Sites and Policies Plan 2014.
